{
  "text": "The Genome Analysis Toolkit (GATK) software was employed to identify SNPs [CITATION_1] . All the clean reads were used to identify SNPs according to [CITATION_2] . In brief, validated SNP site must have two and only two SNP-types. Reads from these two SNP-types must account for ≥90% of the total reads that align to this SNP site. Each SNP-type must have ≥3 reads and the reads account for ≥20% of the total reads on that SNP site [CITATION_3] . For each SNP, Bayes' theorem was approached to estimate the linkage probability between a SNP and the causal gene [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
